            <div type="general">
               <head>General</head>
               <p>Because of the city’s location on the Mediterranean coast, Jaffa has played an important role throughout history. Its port was an important strategic stronghold and therefore the city suffered frequent changes in rule.</p>
               <p>Today it is part of the greater Tel Aviv-Jaffa area. Tel Aviv had been only a suburb of Jaffa; but due to their fast growth, the two towns were united in 1950.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="researchHistory">
               <head>Research history</head>
               <p>The linguistic investigations of Uri Horesh
                 mainly deal with phonology. In one of his publications <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:RLZKWZVZ">(Horesh
                 2000)</rs> he considers the question of whether or not, based upon
                 phonemic and phonetic criteria, the city’s variety is a typical urban
                 Palestinian dialect. In another article, he examines the influence of
                 Modern Hebrew on the Arabic of Jaffe <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:48VWC9IQ">(Horesh 2014)</rs>.</p>

               <p><rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:EBJYZ3VH">Arnold (2004)</rs> is
               a short phonological and morphological overview of the Arabic in Jaffa
               and surrounding villages. <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:NPJ679RJ">Arnold (2015)</rs> provides
               a sample text with English translation.</p>

               <p>Because of the founding of Israel in 1948, the
               majority of the Arabs living in Jaffa had to flee to the Gaza Strip.
               <rs type="bibl" ref="profile:profile_gaza_01">The profile of Gaza</rs> provides
               further information on the dialect contact there.</p>
            </div>

